    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To install and use antd in React js, you have to use the  or  package manager that is how you can install the  library‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To install and use antd in React js, you have to use the <code class=\"language-text\">npm</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code> package manager that is how you can install the <code class=\"language-text\">antd</code> library into your project.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to install and use antd in react js.</p>\n<h3>Install Antd</h3>\n<p>Install the following packages to use <code class=\"language-text\">antd</code> in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install antd</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn install antd</code></pre></div>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create a new React JS project.</li>\n<li>Import Antd components.</li>\n<li>Use Antd components in the project.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let‚Äôs start with the first step.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Create a new React JS project.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import Antd components.</h3>\n<p>After installing antd, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Button <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'antd'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Use Antd components in the project.</h3>\n<p>In this blog, see the short example to use <code class=\"language-text\">button</code>  component ant design library.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Button type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"primary\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>Primary<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Button<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>ReactJS use Antd example.</h3>\n<p>This code below is an example, we will import the button component from the ant library, and use button component as a <code class=\"language-text\">primary</code> type of ant design library.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Button <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'antd'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">App</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Button type<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"primary\"</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>Primary<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Button<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 213px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/880a8aa2df1fe09aefd7e349a9bbddda/bc663/antd.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 46.202531645569614%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRl4AAABXRUJQVlA4IFIAAAAQAwCdASoUAAkAPtFWpEuoJKOhsAgBABoJQAALeHMHAsAA341NbrMsFGOZP8Z6a8sZC69NHesw6z8A6/71xsBbqG/rbPiMeC8ND5uNrWPESLAA'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, Antd\"\n        title=\"React, Antd\"\n        src=\"/static/880a8aa2df1fe09aefd7e349a9bbddda/bc663/antd.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/880a8aa2df1fe09aefd7e349a9bbddda/81b7c/antd.webp 158w,\n/static/880a8aa2df1fe09aefd7e349a9bbddda/bc663/antd.webp 213w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 213px) 100vw, 213px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Here, we are provided code sandbox links for the above program to install and use antd in React js. Then you can use whenever you went and do the changes as per your requirements.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aguidehub.com/codesandbox/?code=gracious-solomon-fyopqi\" rel=\"nofollow\"  target=\"_BLANK\" >Try it Yourself</a></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to install and use antd in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"April 06, 2023","description":"Example of install and use antd in React js with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/reactjs.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to install and use accordion in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-04-07-how-to-install-and-use-accordion-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to install and use aos in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-04-05-how-to-install-and-use-aos-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2023-04-06-how-to-install-and-use-antd-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/2023-04-07-how-to-install-and-use-accordion-in-react-js/","nextSlug":"/blog/2023-04-05-how-to-install-and-use-aos-in-react-js/"}},
